  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem requires constructing a bitstring that satisfies prefix-free properties relative to a set of existing bitstrings under truncation rules. This is essentially a variation of the prefix-free code construction problem with specific constraints on how many bits can be removed.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "algorithmic_strategy_designer",
      "instructions": "Analyze the problem constraints: given a set of binary strings, find a way to extend them such that no string is a prefix of another even after any number of bits are removed from the end of the reported IDs. Determine the mathematical condition for 'mistaken identity' under truncation and propose an efficient construction algorithm (e.g., using a Trie or a specific bit-padding strategy) that ensures the extended strings are distinguishable."
    },
    {
      "label": "implementation_specialist",
      "instructions": "Based on the provided algorithmic strategy, write a high-performance Python solution. The solution must handle the large constraints typical of USACO Platinum problems (likely N up to 10^5 and total bits up to 10^6). Ensure the construction is lexicographically minimal if required or simply valid according to the problem's specific extension rules. Focus on time complexity and memory efficiency."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the algorithmic strategy and the implementation to provide the final code and the logic used to ensure no two IDs can be confused under the truncation rule."
}

